data.title: Very good for the price
data.body: You can't beat the sound quality for this price there's actually a fair amount of bass and the sound is pretty rich. These fit my ears better than my $200 Pixel Earbuds pro do. The buttons are weird. There appears to be three, top and bottom buttons but they're not discreet it's a single plastic piece that you can press top, bottom and middle to perform the same functions which are answer/hangup call, play/stop audio, skip/go back tracks. Odd there is no volume control given the button layout but that's my only gripe.

data.title: Best value everyday use or backup.
data.body:
These headphones are workhorses. I have headphones or earbuds in every day, often for hours. They remain comfortable for me like almost no other headphones or earbuds I own, and they sound great. The quality of the audio it shockingly good for how inexpensive they are.

Over time, I've dropped them on sidewalks, and dunked these things in drinks, and eventually worn them out (the mic stopped working after a fall from a balcony, but the audio was still decent). They're so good, I've now got three replacement pairs in the drawer and the current ones I'm using now. I love these earbuds. They are a great wired option!

data.title: Indestructible
data.body: I mostly use these at work as part of "hearing protection" and they work great, I can listen to an audiobook at 70% volume and not hear the screaming machine next to me. The bass is lacking but the mids and highs are nice and clear. They're also indestructible, my one pair went through multiple wash/dry cycles and daily hard snags on the cord and they lasted well over a year. Best bang for a buck.

data.title: These are good sound and very discrete
data.body: I love these earbuds and they are very hard to find. They have a discreet wire that sits under the throat connecting the earbuds, and if you have hair that covers your ears, people don't know you are even wearing them. They last about 3 hours tops, not 6 like they list. When you get them, use them and let them run all the way down and make sure they don't konk out when the icon on your phone shows there is still supposed to be 50% power. That's the only thing, check them out as soon as you get them and exchange them if the icon doesn't show the power nearing 0% on the little battery indicator on your phone. I figured out some people are returning them after significant use and the company possibly resells them not knowing what happened. Most sets are great and they have lasted me at least 2+ years. Also, don't brush your teeth with them in, you can accidently drip toothpaste in the charger and it ruins them, lol.

data.title: The best wired ear buds that I've ever purchased!
data.body: I use these with every phone call because the microphone on my phone itself cuts out, crackles, and is generally speaking...awful. These ear buds solve all of these issues! They have absolutely excellent sound quality, noise cancelling, and the mic is fabulous! I use them every single night to listen to audible books I've already read or listened to while I sleep (tool suggested by my therapist to prevent recurring and almost nightly nightmares... And it has worked for me, in case anyone is wondering lol). Which means that I'd used them much longer and many times over any other pair that I've ever purchased. I've purchased 2 pairs so far, but only because a homeless man at the bus station where I was waiting to pick up a friend was asking everyone if they had a pair of wired ear buds he could possibly have. I'd purchased the first pair a long time ago (years, but I'm not sure how many.) I have several sets of Bluetooth earbuds, so I gave him mine and planned to just get a new pair to help him out. The wires were a little stretched, but they still performed perfectly. In fact, the man that I gave them to came to me after about 30 minutes to ask where I got them because he said that he's never had a pair that had such good audio or mic capability! Pretty awesome! The new pair seems to have even better sound quality than the first, I'm guessing because new and better technology has advanced quite a bit in the years between my purchases (my opinion/assumption... I'm not a scientist or anything so I don't know why for sure, but I AM sure that the new pair of better, though the old pair still would have deserved 5 stars

data.title: Don't Use With iPhones

So if you wear your earbuds in bed like I do, you'll likely end up "butt dialing" someone in your sleep. I‚Äôve accidentally called 3 different people overnight in the week that I‚Äôve had these.
